item.description:
Create an IAM Policy for the Gitlab Runner. In order to be able to deploy our website to an S3 bucket we need to allow our runner to access S3. We do that with an EC2 Instance policy that we attach to our Gitlab Instance.
 In the AWS Console we select from the upper bar &ldquo;Services&rdquo; - &gt; &ldquo;IAM&rdquo;
 In the IAM Page we select &ldquo;Roles&rdquo; From the left side then &ldquo;Create Role&rdquo;.
